	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-09-22T05:33:05">Micro Focus International plc is a United Kingdom-based company, which is engaged in managing mature infrastructure software assets. The Company's products include Micro Focus, such as COBOL Development and Mainframe Solutions, Host Connectivity, Identity Access and Security, Development and IT Operations Management Tools, Collaboration and Networking, and SUSE. SUSE is open source software, which provides Linux and cloud infrastructure solutions. SUSE products enable various organizations across the world across physical, virtual and cloud environments. The SUSE product portfolio includes SUSE Linux Enterprise Server Products, SUSE Linux Enterprise Extensions, SUSE Linux Enterprise Management and Cloud, SUSE OpenStack Cloud, SUSE Enterprise Storage and SUSE Linux Enterprise Desktop. Its professional services include value profile day services, test process modernization, portfolio modernization, value assurance, resource modernization and application health check, among others.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-31T05:18:32">BRIEF: For the six months ended 31 October 2015, Micro Focus International plc revenues increased from $208.3M to $604.5M. Net income increased 73% to $87.5M. Revenues reflect Micro Focus segment increase from $208.3M to $483.3M, SUSE segment increase from $0K to $121.2M. Net income was partially offset by Unallocated segment loss increase from $36M to $113.5M. Dividend per share remained flat at $0.17.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
